-- Turkish banking sector H1 net profit down 8.4 percent -BDDK
-- By Seda Sezer
-- Fri Aug 08, 2014 10:26AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Aug 8 (Reuters) - The Turkish banking sector's net profit fell 8.4 percent year-on-year to 12.5 billion lira ($5.79 billion) in the first half of the year, the banking watchdog BDDK said on Friday.

The sector's loans stood at 1.12 trillion lira at the end of the first half from the end of last year, watchdog data showed.